msgstr ""

#: ../../../advertising/ad-customization.rst:8
msgid ""
"This document details features that are a **work in progress**. To discuss "
"this document, please get in touch in the `issue tracker`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advertising/ad-customization.rst:13
msgid ""
"In addition to allowing users and documentation authors to :ref:`opt out "
"<advertising/ethical-advertising:Opting out>` of advertising, we allow some "
"additional controls for documentation authors to control the positioning and "
"styling of advertising. This can improve the performance of advertising or "
"make sure the ad is in a place where it fits well with the documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advertising/ad-customization.rst:22
msgid "Controlling the placement of an ad"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advertising/ad-customization.rst:24
msgid ""
"It is possible for a documentation author to instruct Read the Docs to "
"position advertising in a specific location. This is done by adding a "
"specific element to the generated body. The ad will be inserted into this "
"container wherever this element is in the document body."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advertising/ad-customization.rst:29
msgid "<div id=\"ethical-ad-placement\"></div>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advertising/ad-customization.rst:35
msgid "In Sphinx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advertising/ad-customization.rst:37
msgid ""
"In Sphinx, this is typically done by adding a new template (under "
"`templates_path`_) for inclusion in the `HTML sidebar`_ in your ``conf.py``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advertising/ad-customization.rst:44
msgid ""
"## In conf.py\n"
"html_sidebars = {\n"
"    \"**\": [\n"
"        \"localtoc.html\",\n"
"        \"ethicalads.html\",  # Put the ad below the navigation but above "
"previous/next\n"
"        \"relations.html\",\n"
"        \"sourcelink.html\",\n"
"        \"searchbox.html\",\n"
"    ]\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

